   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "# Quick Guide\n",
    "\n",
    "Import the multitool library a start working with its help in tasks such as those mentioned here below:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import molmodmt as molmodmt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fetching molecular systems from web databases\n",
    "\n",
    "You probably don't remember how to fetch a pdb from the protein data bank to be loaded in your script as a parmed, pdbfixer, mdtraj, nglview, pytraj or mdanalysis native object -just to mention some-. MolModMT has a unique command to do it:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "system_parmed     = molmodmt.fetch('pdb:1sux',form='parmed')\n",
    "system_pdbfixer   = molmodmt.fetch('pdb:1sux',form='pdbfixer')\n",
    "system_mdtraj     = molmodmt.fetch('pdb:1sux',form='mdtraj')\n",
    "system_mdanalysis = molmodmt.fetch('pdb:1sux',form='mdanalysis')\n",
    "system_nglview    = molmodmt.fetch('pdb:1sux',form='nglview')\n",
    "system_pytraj     = molmodmt.fetch('pdb:1sux',form='pytraj')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The class, or in MolModMT syntaxis, the form of each object can be checked as:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "parmed.Structure\n",
      "pdbfixer.PDBFixer\n",
      "mdtraj.Trajectory\n",
      "mdanalysis.Universe\n",
      "nglview\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(molmodmt.get_form(system_parmed))\n",
    "print(molmodmt.get_form(system_pdbfixer))\n",
    "print(molmodmt.get_form(system_mdtraj))\n",
    "print(molmodmt.get_form(system_mdanalysis))\n",
    "print(molmodmt.get_form(system_nglview))\n",
    "print(molmodmt.get_form(system_pytraj))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "## Molecular systems as MolModMT's forms\n",
    "\n",
    "MolModMT's works with methods as `load` or `convert` over different forms of a  molecular model. This way, the same molecular model can take de form of a pdb file, a parmed structure or a pytraj object. In order to list the different forms MolModMT currently recognize, check the method `info_forms`:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'engines': ['mdanalysis',\n",
       "  'mdtraj',\n",
       "  'modeller',\n",
       "  'native',\n",
       "  'openmm',\n",
       "  'parmed',\n",
       "  'pdbfixer'],\n",
       " 'classes': ['mdanalysis.Universe',\n",
       "  'mdtraj.Topology',\n",
       "  'mdtraj.Trajectory',\n",
       "  'modeller.Modeller',\n",
       "  'moldyn.Native',\n",
       "  'molsys.Native',\n",
       "  'openmm.Positions',\n",
       "  'openmm.Topology',\n",
       "  'parmed.Structure',\n",
       "  'pdbfixer.PDBFixer',\n",
       "  'yank.Topography'],\n",
       " 'files': ['dcd', 'ddb', 'h5', 'mol2', 'pdb', 'sdf', 'smi', 'xtc'],\n",
       " 'ids': ['pdb:id']}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 36,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
